definition.value: Any estranoid where the estrane is conjugated.
Any pregnane derivative where the pregnane is conjugated.
Any saccharolipid having one or more sugars bound to fatty acyl chain(s).
Any fatty acyl-L-carnitine where the fatty acid has 2 or more unsaturations. Major species at pH 7.3
A heterodetic cyclic peptide with formula C26H39N5O12S produced by Ustilaginoidea virens fungi. It is an inhibitor of microtubule assembly.
Any dicarboxylic acid carrying a hydroxy group on the carbon atom at position alpha to the carboxy group. Major species at pH 7.3.
Any glycerophosphocholine having an oxidized fatty acyl component. Major species at pH 7.3.
Any 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine that has an oxidized fatty acyl component. Major species at pH 7.3.
Any 2-acylglycerol where the fatty acyl component is oxidized.
Any N-acylethanolamine having an oxidized fatty acyl component.
Any lysoglycerophosphocholine having an oxidized fatty acyl chain at sn-2. Major species at pH 7.3.
Any 2-acylglycerophosphoethanolamine having an oxidized fatty acyl chain at position 2. Major species at pH 7.3.
Any disaccharide composed of 2 galactose moieties.

A sulfoglycolipid in which alpha,alpha-trehalose, sulfated at the 2'-position, is acylated at the 2-position with palmitoic acid, and at the 3-position with (2E,4S,6S,8S)-2,4,6,8-tetramethylhexadec-2-enoic acid.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of quillaic acid, resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group; Major species at pH 7.3.
A beta-D-glucoside that is quillaic acid in which the carboxy group at position 28 is substituted by a beta-D-glucopyranoside group.
A  morphinane alkaloid found in the opium poppy, Papaver somniferum var. album; has analgesic, anti-tussive and anti-diarrhoeal properties.
A methyl ketone that is nonan-2-one carrying a double bond at position 5.
A phosphatidylcholine having an alpha-linolenoyl at sn-2 and a fatty acyl chain of unknown composition at sn-1. Major species at pH 7.3.
A phosphatidylcholine having an alpha-linolenoyl at sn-1 and a fatty acyl chain of unknown composition at sn-2. Major species at pH 7.3.
A phosphatidylcholine having a linoleoyl at sn-1 and a fatty acyl chain of unknown composition at sn-2. Major species at pH 7.3.
